name: PHP Image Cache
author: Tobias Nyholm

sections.description:
This plugin cache images with PHP. Other cache plugins depends on your server settings. If you don’t have the appropriate server settings enabled, then your images will not be cached with the other cache plugins.

With this plugin you are forcing the images to be cached and your page will load much faster for returning visitors.
For more information see installation page or the
Webfish homepage.
sections.installation:
This is some brief installation notes. For more information see Webfish

  1. Upload the plugin source to the /wp-content/plugins/ directory
  2. Activate the plugin through the ‘Plugins’ menu in WordPress
sections.faq: The frequently asked questions is updated at the plugin’s homepage PHP Image Cache.
sections.changelog: You will find the change log at Webfish

short_description: This plugin cache images with PHP and does not depend on your server settings like other cahce plugin does.
